        // About
        section.about-section.grey-background.text-center
            .inner-section
                .container.px-4.px-lg-5
                    .row.gx-4.gx-lg-5.justify-content-center
                        .col-xl-6.col-12.about-container
                            img.img-fluid(src='assets/gallery/about/sunset.jpg', alt='...')
                        .col-xl-6.col-12.about-container.align-vertically
                            h3.mb-4 "My work is inspired by the sea, skies and landscape of Knapdale, Argyll, where I spend as much time as I can walking, exploring, absorbing and storing up ideas for paintings."


        section.about-section.white-background.text-center
            .inner-section
                .container.px-4.px-lg-5
                    .row.gx-4.gx-lg-5.justify-content-center
                        .col-xl-6.col-12.about-container.align-vertically
                            p "I use oil paint to express my experience of the sea, the sky, and the land in-between. My painting process is intuitive and is informed by what I call my "heart response" or "felt-sense", my internal landscape's reflection on the external landscape, as opposed to a striving for a figurative or literal depiction. In the work I am investigating a visual language, using colour, texture and mark-making to convey a powerful elemental energy.
                        .col-xl-6.col-12.about-container
                            img.img-fluid(src='assets/gallery/about/sky.jpg', alt='...')


        section.about-section.grey-background.text-center
            .inner-section
                .container.px-4.px-lg-5
                    .row.gx-4.gx-lg-5.justify-content-center
                        .col-xl-6.col-12.about-container
                            img.img-fluid(src='assets/gallery/about/sea.jpg', alt='...')
                        .col-xl-6.col-12.about-container.align-vertically
                            p I am trying to capture an expansiveness, a spaciousness or other worldliness, the ephemeral quality of the ever-changing light, the weather, my emotional response, and the magic that this remote, largely unpopulated landscape elicits in me. I am inviting the viewer to enter the space I have created and reconnect with their own experiential memories of being surrounded by the vastness of nature."


        section.about-section.white-background.text-center
